Sequence Information.Peptide Name: DYNQPNS lipopeptide (natural AMPs; lactone; depsipeptide, XXL; XXJ; UCSB1f; fatty acid cyclized lipopeptides; Gram-positive bacteria, prokaryotes)

Literature Information.Literature: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals this sequence is most similar (30.77%) toMyxinidinChemical modification: a lactone is formed from the C-terminal carboxylic group to the hydroxyl group of a 3-hydroxylated C18 fatty acid.Activity: active against Gram+ S. aureus MTCC1430, B. subtilis MTCC121 5 out of 7 strains, M. luteus MTCC106, and fungus A. terreus Lab isolate.
Literature Information.Author: Baindara P, Mandal SM, Chawla N, Singh PK, Pinnaka AK, Korpole S.2013
Literature Information.Title: Characterization of two antimicrobial peptides produced by a halotolerant Bacillus subtilis strain SK.DU.4 isolated from a rhizosphere soil sample.
